In the process of assembling reaction wheels onto a satellite, it is impractical to mount them perfectly aligned. So, the misalignment effect of the reaction wheels should be considered in the dynamic equation of the satellite. Figure 2 illustrates the alignment errors of each reaction wheel. So, the Euler equation of the satellite (1) with actuator misalignment can be expressed as:Fig. 2
